"'''Skywalkers'''" is a 40-page comic featured in ''[[Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures Volume 2]]''. It was written by [[W. Haden Blackman|Haden Blackman]], with [[George Lucas]] credited for dialogue taken from [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']]. The art was by the [[Fillbach Brothers]]. [[Wil Glass]] provided the coloring. [[Michael David Thomas]] is responsible for the lettering.

==Plot summary==
{{Plot|comic}}

[[File:Luke_CWA.jpg|thumb|left|Luke Skywalker|150px]]
On [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], in the year [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] asks [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] about his father. Obi-Wan has a flashback to the [[Battle of Terra Sool]], during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], many years previous. [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] and Obi-Wan were helping the [[Terra Sool militia]] to overthrow the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] occupation. When the Separatists attempted to ravage the [[Planet/Legends|planet]], Anakin destroyed a barrage of Separatist missiles, with Obi-Wan remarking that "[The] learner has become the master." The story returns to the "present," where, onboard the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star I]], [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] looks down upon the clothes that he believes are all that remain of his former master.

